      "name": "Vishal Alhat",
      "title": "Developer Advocate",
      "organization": "Amazon Web Services",
      "talk_title": "TBA",
      "abstract": "TBA",
      "bio": "A Developer Advocate at Amazon Web Services (AWS), he focuses on empowering builders and scaling technical communities across Asia Pacific, Japan, and China. With over a decade of experience in software development, DevOps, and cybersecurity, he brings a strong practitioner’s perspective to developer advocacy. His approach is rooted in deep technical empathy—understanding real-world developer challenges and championing their success within AWS by bridging the gap between builders and cloud services.\n\nHis journey is strongly grounded in community leadership, having been recognized as an AWS Hero and AWS Community Builder of the Year. He has led and contributed to prominent user groups including AWS, HashiCorp, and MongoDB, and continues to shape the ecosystem through technical content, international speaking engagements, and active mentorship. Passionate about DevRel, FinOps, and cybersecurity best practices, he is driven by a strong sense of ownership and a personal belief in integrity—ensuring that developer voices meaningfully influence the future of cloud innovation.",
